# AI provider API keys
#
# The workspace automatically tries configured providers in this order:
#   1. Gemini
#   2. OpenAI / ChatGPT
#   3. DeepSeek
# Image OCR is local-first and does NOT use these keys.
# npm install bootstraps PaddleOCR separately through npm run setup:ocr.
#
# You can configure just one key or multiple keys.
# The first provider that is both configured and usable for the current task wins.
#
# Get keys from:
#   Gemini   -> https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
#   OpenAI   -> https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
#   DeepSeek -> https://platform.deepseek.com/api_keys
#
# Local development for the AI assistant:
#   1. Copy this file to .env
#   2. Fill in one or more real AI API keys
#   3. Run `npm run dev`
#
# Cloud deployment (Cloud Run / VPS / container):
#   Configure the same keys in the platform environment variables.
#   server.ts reads them at runtime and keeps the raw keys on the server.
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_key_here
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_key_here
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=your_deepseek_key_here